- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses end-to-end speech recognition using sequence-to-sequence networks and CTC objective function, which are common techniques in natural language processing.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition and acoustic units.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for speech recognition.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of AI techniques for speech recognition.
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is a possible category as the paper deals with processing speech signals.
